WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.500
Welcome to this lecture on introductory computer science concepts.

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:09.000
Today we will be covering the fundamentals of algorithms and data structures.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:13.800
An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for solving a problem or accomplishing a task.

00:00:13.800 --> 00:00:18.500
Data structures are ways of organizing and storing data so that it can be accessed efficiently.

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:23.000
Together, these two concepts form the backbone of modern software engineering.
